Class CCAddressBookUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.contact.CCAddressBookUtil

  • public class CCAddressBookUtil
extends java.lang.Object
    This class adds some ClaimCenter specific behavior to the methods in AddressBookUtil.

    • Method Detail

      • updateAddressBook

        @Deprecated
public static void updateAddressBook(Location webLocation,
                                                 ExternalContactSource externalContactSource,
                                                 Contact contact)
        Deprecated. As of ClaimCenter 8.0 deleting/editing AB contacts is deprecated
        Updates an external contact source with the given contact. Revalidates the given location first, and commits changes on success. This update includes all relationships, including non-primary ones.

      • updateAddressBookContact

        @Deprecated
public static void updateAddressBookContact(Location webLocation,
                                                        ExternalContactSource externalContactSource,
                                                        Contact contact,
                                                        boolean onlyPrimaryRelationships)
        Deprecated. As of ClaimCenter 8.0 deleting/editing AB contacts is deprecated
        Updates an external contact source with the given contact. Revalidates the given location first, and commits changes on success.
        Parameters:
        webLocation - the current Location. This is used as context to get the current bundle and select UI elements.
        externalContactSource - a source for loading the contact with.
        contact - the contact to update
        onlyPrimaryRelationships - true if only primary relationships should be updated, otherwise all relationships will be updated

      • updateAddressBookContact

        @Deprecated
public static void updateAddressBookContact(Location webLocation,
                                                        ExternalContactSource externalContactSource,
                                                        Contact contact,
                                                        boolean onlyPrimaryRelationships,
                                                        ExternalContact externalContact)
        Deprecated. As of ClaimCenter 8.0 deleting/editing AB contacts is deprecated
        Updates an external contact source with the given contact. Revalidates the given location first, and commits changes on success. Also creates a ContactAutoSyncWorkItem to ensure that any auto sync enabled contacts in CC get updated with this change.
        Parameters:
        webLocation - the current Location. This is used as context to get the current bundle and select UI elements.
        externalContact - the original contact, e.g. in ContactManager
        externalContactSource - the external contact source
        contact - the contact to update
        onlyPrimaryRelationships - true if only primary relationships should be updated, otherwise all relationships will be updated

      • deleteContact

        @Deprecated
public static void deleteContact(Contact contact,
                                             Location webLocation)
        Deprecated. As of ClaimCenter 8.0 deleting/editing AB contacts is deprecated
        Delete contact and leave this page.

        If the current page is a popup, we go up the stack. Else we always go to the AddressBookSearch page.

      • deleteContacts

        @Deprecated
public static void deleteContacts(Contact[] checkedValues,
                                              java.util.Map displayableErrorMap)
        Deprecated. As of ClaimCenter 8.0 deleting/editing AB contacts is deprecated
        Delete an array of contacts from the addressbook. Contacts that cannot be deleted because of InsufficientPermissionException are added to the displayableErrorMap. But the rest are deleted.
        Parameters:
        checkedValues - Array of Contacts to delete that are provided by the CheckedValuesActionConfig.CHECKED_VALUES. Cannot be Null.
        displayableErrorMap - is the map {Key=Object,value=UserDisplayableException} that provides feedback to the CheckedValuesToolbarButtonWidgetConfig. Cannot be Null.

      • linkToMatch

        public static void linkToMatch(AddressBookMatch addressBookMatch,
                               Contact contact)
        Links the contact to the addressbookmatch.

        NOTE: This is a *very* specialized method that makes the following assumptions about the environment in which it is called:

        • It is called from within a worksheet that will be closed by this method.
        • The top screen is the bundle in which to edit the addressBookMatch
        Parameters:
        addressBookMatch - the addressBookMatch to be linked to
        contact - the contact to be linked

      • createMatchInAddressBook

        public static void createMatchInAddressBook(AddressBookMatch addressBookMatch,
                                            boolean onlyPrimaryRelationships)
        Creates the contact in addressbook.

        NOTE: This is a *very* specialized method that makes the following assumptions about the environment in which it is called:

        • It is called from within a worksheet that will be closed by this method.
        • The top screen is the bundle in which to edit the addressBookMatch
        Parameters:
        addressBookMatch - contains the local contact to use for creating the addressbook contact. If addressBookMatch is a DefinitiveMatch then there must be zero matches.
        onlyPrimaryRelationships - create only primary relationships as defined in contact-sync-config.xml

      • closeActiveWorksheet

        public static void closeActiveWorksheet()
        Close the current active worksheet. (For use on ContactMatch worksheet when the "Link to" button is clicked)

      • isSyncableRelationship

        @Deprecated
public static boolean isSyncableRelationship(ContactBidiRel bidiRel,
                                                         IEntityType contactSubtype)
        Deprecated. Since CC 8.0.0. use ContactSystemUtil.isSyncableRelationship instead
        Check to see in contact-sync-config.xml if for a contact subtype a certain bidiRel is syncable. For example, out-of-the-box the a Person's Guardian is syncable, but a Person's primaryContact is not.

        This method is not yet used out-of-the-box, but can be used by customers in the ClaimContactRelatedContactsLV.pcf to indicate which relationships are going to be synced. (Potential UI improvement)

        Deprecated. Since CC 8.0.0.
        For PolicyCenter only.
